headline: Rising Tariffs Challenge Williams-Sonoma But Diversified Model Supports Growth, Says Analyst
summary: Williams-Sonoma, Inc. (NYSE:WSM) shares are trading lower on Thursday. On Wednesday, the retailer reported revenue of $1.84 billion, a 2.7% increase from the same quarter last year and ahead of Wall Street’s estimate of $1.83 billion. Comparable brand revenue rose 3.7% year over year. Also Read: What’s Going On With Dell Stock Thursday? headline: WSM Q2 Deep Dive: Tariff Headwinds and Innovation Shape Outlook
summary: Kitchenware and home goods retailer Williams-Sonoma (NYSE:WSM) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 2.7% year on year to $1.84 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2 per share was 10.5% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
